The problem with the FIDONET mail routing loops that was described is
not really with the MX; it is with the gateways.

A gateway fronting for a fidonet region must recognize the subset of
hosts that it is fronting for and route those to the appropriate mailer,
rather than to the central router.

This should be no harder than to define a class enumerating those
fidonet hosts, and point that class to wahtever mailer is used to reach
those hosts.

